						<div class="postbody">That's why I said "kinda" backwards. What's more confusing to a newbie, IMO, is that the first time the NMI runs there are no updates to do, because the frame logic hasn't run yet. To work around that you have to implement a "FrameReady" or "FirstFrame" flag, to skip the first session of VRAM updates.</div>

